                     <interp inst="def1-1957-18420613" type="surname" value="PURDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1957-18420613" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">MARY PURDY</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18420613-1957-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18420613-1957-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420613-1957-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18420613-cd-220" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420613-1957-offence-1 t18420613-cd-220"></join>17th of June</rs>, 2 lb. 14 oz. weight of mutton, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18420613-name-1260" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1260" type="surname" value="BOTTRILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1260" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1260" type="occupation" value="butcher"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420613-1957-offence-1 t18420613-name-1260"></join>William Bot<lb></lb>trill</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1261" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1261" type="surname" value="GULLARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1261" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN GULLARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Bottrill, butcher, of Rochester-row, Westminster. On the 17th of June, I saw the prisoner outside our shop—she took the mutton from the board, and my master took it away from her, when she had got about thirty yards—I saw him take it from</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184206130211"></xptr>
               <p>under her cloak—she said she was very sorry, and did not know how she came to do it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PRENDERGAST</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Had she bought any thing? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, one piece—I am sure she did not buy this piece—my mistress is not here, nor my master—the prisoner had paid my mistress for one piece, which came to sixpence—that piece was in her basket—I have been a witness in the Old Court before—I got more than 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. by that—I did not say that I liked such jobs as these, to my knowledge—I cannot swear that I did not—the prisoner's daughter and sons were joking with me over the way in a public-house, and I said I did not know whe<lb></lb>ther there was a God or not, as I bad never seen him—I said that, be<lb></lb>cause I was asked the question—I was asked a great many questions by the whole of them—they had been trying to make me tipsy—I have known the prisoner to come to my master as a customer for four years—the lives in the neighbourhood—I saw my master yesterday rooming—he said he did not wish to prosecute the prisoner—he said yesterday that he did not want to have any thing to do with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1262" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1262" type="surname" value="CORNISH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1262" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM CORNISH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable B</hi> 35.) I took the prisoner—she said she was very sorry for what she had done, and hoped the prosecutor would forgive her.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did she not say she did not mean to steal it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> She said she did not intend to steal any thing—I found 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on her.</p>
